      • getLevelDifference

        public int getLevelDifference()
        Given that a floor is a collection of areas on a similar altitude of a structure, the level difference is the difference in floors between the beginning and the end of the NavigationEvent Step. If the NavigationSegment does not change floors then the default value is zero(0). Moving down to a lower floor decrements the value by one(1). Moving up to a higher floor increments the value by one(1).
        Returns:
        levelDifference - {Typeof Integer}

      • getType

        public java.lang.String getType()
        A String value which represents the type of medium on which the NavigationEvent is performed. Values may include, but are not limited to, the following: Walking, Stairs, Elevator, Escalator, Train, Ramp, or Bus. By default the medium of navigation is assumed to be Walking.
        Returns:
        type - {Typeof String}
